webpackJsonp([0xecae28f0f286],{388:function(e,A){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 1560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="mural slicer detail"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1-8316c.png"\n        srcset="/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1-e4a0f.png 400w,\n/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1-2c787.png 800w,\n/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1-8316c.png 1560w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 1560px) 100vw, 1560px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<p>After I got an AxiDraw I wanted to combine it with the Vive tracking experiments I was doing at the\ntime. I had written a server in Unity <!-- TODO upload to GitHub and link it -->to broadcast the\ntracking information from Vive controllers to other applications over UDP. So I wrote a simple web\napplication that took a vector image and sliced out an AxiDraw-sized region based on the location\nof a Vive controller I crudely zip-tied to the plotter.</p>\n<p>Sizing and placing the image in real space was a pain and I didn\'t have time to make that better so\nI only did a few tests before shelving the project. To use it I would load the image and manually\ntweak the code to scale and place it on my floor. Then I would pull the trigger on the Vive controller\nto tell the application to send the commands for drawing the current slice of the image to the AxiDraw.\nAfter plotting a region was finished I would move the machine and trigger it again.</p>\n<p>A lot could be improved with this rough prototype. The accuracy of the output was much poorer than\nthe accuracy of the tracking because I didn\'t accurately map the virtual image region to the\nmachine space for the AxiDraw. As a result the lines at the edges of different regions didn\'t\ncompletely meet. But overall I was happy that the basic principles were sound, and in later projects\nat Artmatr and my robotics company, <a href="https://haploid.co" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Haploid</a>, I extended the concept much further\nwith significantly more complicated machines.</p>\n<p>You can find the code I wrote for slicing out portions of the image to be plotted, and the front-end\nI used to display it, on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/jmptable/axidraw-mural-slicer" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">jmptable/axidraw-mural-slicer</a></p>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 1600px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 205.96330275229357%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="mural slicer"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/mural-slicer-27498da52b549d81eefec6f6c1dc7fb4-ee623.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/mural-slicer-27498da52b549d81eefec6f6c1dc7fb4-51a12.jpg 400w,\n/static/mural-slicer-27498da52b549d81eefec6f6c1dc7fb4-b1745.jpg 800w,\n/static/mural-slicer-27498da52b549d81eefec6f6c1dc7fb4-ee623.jpg 1600w,\n/static/mural-slicer-27498da52b549d81eefec6f6c1dc7fb4-3353e.jpg 1744w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>',frontmatter:{title:"Plotting Images Bigger than the Plotter",date:"03.06.2017",description:"Tracking an AxiDraw with the Vive to draw images larger than the machine piecemeal",cover:{publicURL:"/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1.png",childImageSharp:{resize:{src:"/static/mural-slicer-detail-d018a63603ca09cfbf394d75c82aa7b1-f6604.png"}}}},fields:{slug:"/plotting-images-bigger-than-the-plotter"},excerpt:"After I got an AxiDraw I wanted to combine it with the Vive tracking experiments I was doing at the\ntime. I had written a server in Unityâ€¦"}},pathContext:{slug:"/plotting-images-bigger-than-the-plotter"}}}});
